## üîß Build from Source

### Prerequisites
```bash
# Install .NET 8.0 SDK
wget https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/22.04/packages-microsoft-prod.deb -O packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo dpkg -i packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y dotnet-sdk-8.0

# Install dependencies
sudo apt-get install -y build-essential cmake git
```

### Build Instructions
```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/CrownParkComputing/switchtoolkitandroid.git
cd switchtoolkitandroid

# Build for Linux
dotnet publish src/SwitchToolkit/SwitchToolkit.csproj \
  -r linux-x64 \
  -c Release \
  -p:PublishSingleFile=true \
  -p:SelfContained=true

# Run the application
./bin/Release/net8.0/linux-x64/SwitchToolkit
```

## üêõ Known Issues

### Current Limitations
- **No GUI**: Command-line only interface in alpha builds
- **File Permissions**: May require elevated permissions for some operations
- **Emulator Integration**: Limited testing with Linux emulators
- **Audio**: Missing audio feedback features

### Planned Fixes
- **GUI Development**: Complete desktop interface implementation
- **Permission Handling**: Improve file access without root privileges
- **Audio Support**: System notifications and sound effects
- **DPI Scaling**: Support for high-DPI displays

