## ‚ùì FAQ

### Q: When will Linux support be available?
A: We target a public beta in Q2 2026 and stable release in Q3 2026. Progress depends on testing feedback and community support.

### Q: Will it work on ARM devices like Raspberry Pi?
A: Yes, we plan to support ARM64 architecture, including Raspberry Pi 4/5 and similar devices.

### Q: Can I help with development?
A: Absolutely! We're looking for contributors with Linux experience. Join our Discord or check our GitHub for contributing guidelines.

### Q: What about Steam Deck support?
A: Yes! Steam Deck support is planned for the Linux release, leveraging its Linux-based SteamOS.

